      "writtenOn": "2021-06-21T17:07:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I worry that if KeepAliveMeetingPoint does not get called, the whole test will not terminate.\n\nWhat about a pattern like this:\n\nctx, cancel :\u003d context.WithCancel(context.Background())\ndefer cancel()\n\nkeepAliveCallCount :\u003d int32(0)\nswitchboardMock.On(\"KeepAliveMeetingPoint\", testutils.AnyContext, meetingPoint).Run(func(args mock.Arguments) { atomic.AddInt32(\u0026keepAliveCallCount, 1)}))\n\n...\n\ngo c.singleStep(ctx, time.NewTicker(time.Microsecond), time.Microsecond)\nassert.Eventually(t, func() bool { return atomic.LoadIn32(\u0026keepAliveCallCount) \u003e\u003d 1 }, time.Second, 10*time.Millisecond)\nswitchboardMock.AssertExpectations(t)\n\nThat way, if the callback does not happen in a reasonable time, we fail the test instead of running forever or timeout.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 61,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 61,
        "endChar": 10
      },
      "revId": "ed5ededc176bbea982d98b8879c4c90c81c9d6a0",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2ba317cf_3c15d914",
        "filename": "machine/go/machine/targetconnect/targetconnect_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 61,
      "author": {
        "id": 5205
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-21T17:21:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Both Connection.switchboard and Connection.revPortForward are mocks, so there\u0027s no chance of a timeout in this test, either it passes or it fails. Sure, if there\u0027s a bug it will deadlock, and the test will timeout after 60s, but at that point it means there\u0027s a bug in the code that needs to be fixed.",
      "parentUuid": "43fee3cd_779c2ff1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 61,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 61,
        "endChar": 10
      },
      "revId": "ed5ededc176bbea982d98b8879c4c90c81c9d6a0",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
